cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM 

The paper deals with the problem of dense segmentation of histology images using convolutional neural networks. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of multi-scale information and its impact on segmentation performance, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of publicly available datasets and the focus on image analysis also suggest the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which is a common topic in multimedia (cs.MM).
